      "content": "The fourth principle of Open-Source Capitalism is making open source investable. By enabling investor flows through the Operational Collateral Fund (OCF), open-source projects gain sustainable funding channels. Returns are tied to the downstream use of open infrastructure. The OCF allocates resources to high-potential initiatives and rewards contributors by issuing POWTs, building trust among contributors and investors through transparent allocation processes.",
